1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §1730-B is enacted to read:
3 §1730-B. Health Information Technology Fund
4 The Health Information Technology Fund, referred to in this section as "the fund," is
5 established within the department.
6 1. Use of fund. The fund must be used to support the operation and sustainability of
7 a state-designated statewide health information exchange operated in accordance with
8 section 1711-C, subsection 18 and to meet the State's matching fund requirements to obtain
9 federal funding to support the operation and sustainability of such an exchange. Funds
10 received pursuant to subsection 2 may be used only for purposes directly related to the
11 operation and sustainability of a state-designated statewide health information exchange.
12 The department shall administer the fund in a manner that maximizes eligibility for
13 available federal matching funds.
14 2. Source of funds; separate account; interest; nonlapsing fund. The fund is
15 administered by the department. The fund consists of money appropriated or allocated by
16 the Legislature, federal funds, grants, gifts and other funds from public or private sources.
17 The fund must be held separate and apart from all other money, funds and accounts.
18 Interest earned by the fund must be credited to the fund. Any unexpended balances
19 remaining in the fund at the end of the fiscal year do not lapse and must be carried forward
20 to the next fiscal year.
21 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
